WEBVTT

00:08.921 --> 00:09.270
.

00:09.313 --> 00:11.098
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:11.141 --> 00:12.403
the people are represented

00:12.447 --> 00:14.797
by two separate,
yet equally important groups:

00:14.840 --> 00:16.755
the police,
who investigate crime,

00:16.799 --> 00:19.715
and the district attorneys,
who prosecute the offenders.

00:19.758 --> 00:21.717
These are their stories.

00:24.981 --> 00:28.245
- No, no, no, leave those.

00:28.289 --> 00:29.812
I'll take care of it.

00:29.855 --> 00:31.335
I promised your mom
I wouldn't let you be late.

00:31.379 --> 00:34.077
- It's all right.
I'm carpooling with Annie.

00:34.121 --> 00:35.513
Her mom's picking me up.

00:35.557 --> 00:36.645
- Did you finish that
"Scarlet Letter" thing?

00:36.688 --> 00:38.951
The homework thing?
- Yes, Dad.

00:38.995 --> 00:42.825
And I'm ready for the
math test, so stop worrying.

00:42.868 --> 00:44.609
- You'll understand one day.

00:44.653 --> 00:47.525
- I already do.

00:47.569 --> 00:49.614
They're almost here.
Bye, I love you.

00:49.658 --> 00:50.572
- Love you.

00:50.615 --> 00:52.182
Love you more.
- [giggles]

00:52.226 --> 00:54.706
- Love you the most.
- [laughs]

00:54.750 --> 00:57.666
[sentimental music]

00:57.709 --> 01:04.629
♪

01:16.250 --> 01:17.860
[phone buzzes]

01:20.210 --> 01:22.212
- Yeah, Jalen, what's up?

01:22.256 --> 01:25.694
[tense music]

01:25.737 --> 01:29.001
♪

01:29.045 --> 01:31.439
- Somebody really put
this poor girl through it.

01:31.482 --> 01:34.137
Based on rigor, she died
within the last eight hours.

01:34.181 --> 01:35.225
Multiple stab wounds.

01:35.269 --> 01:36.748
No obvious signs
of sex assault,

01:36.792 --> 01:38.837
but petechial hemorrhages
in the eyes

01:38.881 --> 01:40.970
indicate neck compression.

01:41.013 --> 01:42.928
More later.
- ID?

01:42.972 --> 01:44.452
Bag her hands.

01:48.456 --> 01:50.240
- Not a lot of blood,
considering.

01:50.284 --> 01:52.503
- Could have been stabbed
post-mortem,

01:52.547 --> 01:54.723
killed elsewhere, dumped here.

01:54.766 --> 01:56.420
- What's up with her ear?

01:56.464 --> 01:59.031
- Looks like an earring
was ripped out.

01:59.075 --> 02:00.772
A clump of hair was cut.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.426
- Souvenir collector?

02:02.470 --> 02:04.776
- Let's not get ahead
of ourselves.

02:04.820 --> 02:07.083
It sure would be nice
if we could ID her.

02:07.127 --> 02:11.653
- Detectives, we think
this might be the vic's bag.

02:11.696 --> 02:14.873
- Officer,
you never move evidence.

02:14.917 --> 02:16.788
Give it.
It's too late now.

02:16.832 --> 02:23.230
♪

02:23.273 --> 02:26.146
- Christina Watkins.

02:26.189 --> 02:27.886
That's the author.

02:27.930 --> 02:30.585
- "Cinnamon Girl: My Sweet
and Spicy Life as a Waitress

02:30.628 --> 02:32.108
at a Five Star Restaurant."

02:32.152 --> 02:34.632
- Why would the killer
leave that here?

02:34.676 --> 02:37.374
- Maybe he wanted us to know
that she was somebody.

02:37.418 --> 02:40.508
- A promising young author
making an exciting debut.

02:44.338 --> 02:47.384
[dramatic music]

02:47.428 --> 02:54.565
♪

03:30.471 --> 03:32.647
- Okay, talk to me.

03:32.690 --> 03:34.997
- Our vic is Christina Watkins.
She's 28.

03:35.040 --> 03:37.129
She published a memoir
last month about working

03:37.173 --> 03:38.609
at a downtown restaurant.

03:38.653 --> 03:41.046
She was found by a city
employee at Highbridge Park.

03:41.090 --> 03:45.442
- So uptown, underpopulated,
remote area of the city.

03:45.486 --> 03:47.270
Let me guess, no video?

03:47.314 --> 03:48.706
- And no blood trail.

03:48.750 --> 03:53.320
And no witnesses
who saw how she got there.

03:53.363 --> 03:54.973
- What about a murder weapon?

03:55.017 --> 03:57.193
- Didn't find one,
but wounds indicate

03:57.237 --> 03:59.761
a sharp, angular blade

03:59.804 --> 04:02.851
sharp enough to cut off
some of her hair as well.

04:02.894 --> 04:06.202
- So she was tied up,
and an earring was torn off.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.900
Are we thinking there might
have been a ritual element?

04:08.944 --> 04:10.206
- Not going there yet.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.555
- Do we know
where she was beforehand?

04:11.599 --> 04:12.730
- Working on a timeline.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.297
We found her phone
on Upper Broadway,

04:14.341 --> 04:15.559
four miles
from the crime scene.

04:15.603 --> 04:17.474
It had been run over
a few times.

04:17.518 --> 04:19.737
- Are there any texts,
calls in the cloud

04:19.781 --> 04:21.304
that might tell us
who she was with?

04:21.348 --> 04:23.567
- Just a couple messages
after 10:00.

04:23.611 --> 04:26.353
One for an Uber she canceled
just before midnight,

04:26.396 --> 04:29.660
and another to a Scott Baker,
who seems to be her roommate.

04:29.704 --> 04:32.533
We found this photo of them
together on social media.

04:35.449 --> 04:37.364
- Are those the
same kind of angular blades

04:37.407 --> 04:38.843
as the murder weapon?

04:38.887 --> 04:40.323
- Who is this guy?

04:40.367 --> 04:43.935
- He calls himself
a man with an edge.

04:43.979 --> 04:46.808
[suspenseful music]

04:46.851 --> 04:51.116
♪

04:51.160 --> 04:53.118
- What?

04:53.162 --> 04:54.816
Christina's dead?

04:54.859 --> 04:56.208
That's insane.

04:56.252 --> 04:57.819
- Were you two an item?

04:57.862 --> 04:59.342
- No.

04:59.386 --> 05:02.040
She was all about her writing.

05:02.084 --> 05:03.868
There was a party at the
restaurant where she worked

05:03.912 --> 05:05.130
to celebrate last night.

05:05.174 --> 05:06.393
- Were you there?

05:06.436 --> 05:07.829
- No.

05:07.872 --> 05:10.135
I had to be at my regular
gig at the Flying Hatchet.

05:10.179 --> 05:11.354
- What's that?

05:11.398 --> 05:13.138
- It's an ax throwing bar
in Williamsburg.

05:13.182 --> 05:15.793
- Alcohol and sharp objects.
What could go wrong?

05:15.837 --> 05:17.621
- How late
were you there until?

05:17.665 --> 05:19.231
- 3:00 in the morning.

05:19.275 --> 05:20.668
I'm the manager.
I had to clean up.

05:20.711 --> 05:23.148
- When you got home,
was Christina here?

05:23.192 --> 05:25.063
- No.

05:25.107 --> 05:27.892
I thought she might have hooked
up with someone at the party.

05:27.936 --> 05:30.634
- Do you have a location
of this soiree?

05:30.678 --> 05:32.332
- The Yellow Ribbon.

05:34.116 --> 05:36.771
- I can't believe this.

05:36.814 --> 05:38.599
- When did Christina leave?

05:38.642 --> 05:40.383
- Around midnight, I think?

05:40.427 --> 05:42.777
She was feeling a little off.

05:42.820 --> 05:44.648
- Do you know if she left
with anyone?

05:44.692 --> 05:47.216
- No, but I was
kind of distracted.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.305
There were a lot of VIPs.

05:49.349 --> 05:52.439
People really wanted to come
out and celebrate her success.

05:52.482 --> 05:55.006
She was really beloved
by everyone.

05:55.050 --> 05:56.617
- And nobody gave her
a hard time about what

05:56.660 --> 05:58.009
she wrote in the book?

05:58.053 --> 05:59.620
- Not that I saw.

05:59.663 --> 06:01.099
But I know there
was some commotion

06:01.143 --> 06:03.885
when Tina went out to the
corner to wait for her Uber.

06:06.670 --> 06:11.066
- This is you, 11:50 last night
outside Yellow Ribbon?

06:11.109 --> 06:14.852
- Yeah, I just left the party.
I saw the two of them arguing.

06:14.896 --> 06:15.984
He was--

06:16.027 --> 06:17.464
[scoffs]
Drunk.

06:17.507 --> 06:21.685
He started ranting and raving
at Christina, so I, uh--

06:21.729 --> 06:23.861
- You jumped in to protect her,
is that right?

06:23.905 --> 06:24.949
- Yeah.

06:24.993 --> 06:26.777
Yeah, he was
so aggressive, right?

06:26.821 --> 06:30.085
So I--I pushed him away.
Thankfully, he just walked off.

06:30.128 --> 06:32.217
I'm--I'm no hero, trust me.

06:32.261 --> 06:33.828
I'm not like you guys.

06:35.351 --> 06:37.048
- So, um, when this drunk guy--

06:37.092 --> 06:38.180
- Excuse me.

06:41.096 --> 06:43.098
- After this drunk guy
walked off,

06:43.141 --> 06:44.621
where did Christina go?
Did you see?

06:44.665 --> 06:46.362
Did she hail a cab,
start walking home?

06:46.406 --> 06:47.711
What happened?
- I wish I knew.

06:47.755 --> 06:49.365
I'm not really sure.
- What about you?

06:49.409 --> 06:50.714
Where'd you go?
- Home.

06:50.758 --> 06:52.934
I had a really early
call time this morning.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.979
Yeah.

06:55.023 --> 06:56.894
Um, anything else, guys?

06:56.938 --> 06:59.375
I'm really sorry.
I have to get to set.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.855
- Just one last thing.

07:00.898 --> 07:04.424
The guy who was harassing her,
do you know who he was?

07:04.467 --> 07:06.382
- Yeah, I'm afraid so.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.862
- Why are you afraid?

07:07.905 --> 07:10.038
- Because he's a friend
of mine.

07:10.081 --> 07:12.040
Victor Bernini.

07:12.083 --> 07:13.128
- The chef.

07:15.478 --> 07:17.132
[door buzzes, lock clicks]

07:17.175 --> 07:18.133
[door opens]

07:21.092 --> 07:23.573
- What's up?

07:23.617 --> 07:26.881
- Uh, we--we're looking
for a Victor Bernini?

07:26.924 --> 07:29.231
- Join the club.

07:29.274 --> 07:31.102
- Uh, what does that mean?

07:31.146 --> 07:32.974
- He was supposed to meet me
here around midnight.

07:33.017 --> 07:35.106
He never showed.
- He never showed?

07:35.150 --> 07:36.412
- Mm-hmm.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.936
- Um, do you have any idea
where he would be?

07:38.980 --> 07:42.331
- No, I just crashed here
when he blew me off.

07:42.374 --> 07:43.941
- Hmm.
- Yeah.

07:43.985 --> 07:47.684
To be honest, I actually
don't know him that well.

07:47.728 --> 07:51.601
Uh, we just get together
and party once in a while.

07:54.169 --> 07:57.389
- Did he mention stopping
by his old restaurant

07:57.433 --> 07:59.174
early in the evening?
- Yeah.

07:59.217 --> 08:02.003
Yeah, he seemed
pretty torqued about it.

08:02.046 --> 08:05.006
In fact, he's generally
pretty torqued these days.

08:11.795 --> 08:14.842
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

08:14.885 --> 08:17.453
- So Victor Bernini
is nowhere to be found.

08:17.497 --> 08:20.108
- Well, we're waiting
on cell phone, credit card,

08:20.151 --> 08:21.544
and E-ZPass records.

08:21.588 --> 08:23.241
- And you think
he's a credible suspect?

08:23.285 --> 08:25.983
- Multiple arrests for DUI
and disorderly conduct.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.637
- Plus, he got into an argument
with the vic

08:27.681 --> 08:29.160
shortly before the murder.

08:29.204 --> 08:31.989
- I thought he was some kind
of world-renowned chef.

08:32.033 --> 08:33.817
- He is, but this guy
goes hard in the paint.

08:33.861 --> 08:36.167
I mean, a lot of drugs,
a lot of drinking.

08:36.211 --> 08:38.561
It seems like he's spiraling.
- Meaning?

08:38.605 --> 08:41.172
- He was forced out of his
own restaurant by investors,

08:41.216 --> 08:44.959
and he just declared
personal bankruptcy.

08:45.002 --> 08:46.961
- Okay, so Bernini's
having a rough time.

08:47.004 --> 08:49.398
Why would he go after
Christina Watkins?

08:49.441 --> 08:50.660
- I've been reading her book.

08:50.704 --> 08:53.097
She's not very flattering.

08:53.141 --> 08:55.665
Victor comes off
like a drugged-out sex addict.

08:55.709 --> 08:57.188
- Two days after
that book was published,

08:57.232 --> 08:59.190
that's when he got pushed out
of the restaurant.

08:59.234 --> 09:02.324
And then his staff celebrated
for a week after his exit.

09:02.367 --> 09:05.370
See, the point here is,
Victor is a person of interest.

09:05.414 --> 09:08.373
The sooner we lay hands
on him, the better.

09:08.417 --> 09:09.853
[computer chimes]

09:09.897 --> 09:12.334
- You might not
have to wait that long.

09:12.377 --> 09:13.683
Operations just notified me

09:13.727 --> 09:16.207
there's an EDP job
at Yellow Ribbon.

09:16.251 --> 09:17.774
It's Bernini.

09:17.818 --> 09:21.430
- Okay, guys, watch yourselves.

09:21.473 --> 09:22.823
[tires screeching]

09:22.866 --> 09:25.826
[people screaming]

09:25.869 --> 09:28.045
[tense music]

09:28.089 --> 09:31.309
- Drop it now!
- Let go! Put it down!

09:31.353 --> 09:32.397
- Blue coming through.

09:32.441 --> 09:38.882
♪

09:39.796 --> 09:41.363
Hey, Victor, what's going on?

09:41.406 --> 09:42.843
- Chef!

09:42.886 --> 09:44.714
- Yeah, you got her, Chef.
Put the knife down.

09:44.758 --> 09:45.933
- [breathing heavily]

09:45.976 --> 09:48.762
You've already taken
everything I have.

09:48.805 --> 09:50.633
I'm not letting you
take this place too.

09:50.677 --> 09:52.592
- Hey, hey, Chef.

09:54.071 --> 09:55.246
I'm giving you a choice here.

09:55.290 --> 09:58.380
Now drop the blade,
or I drop you.

09:58.423 --> 10:00.730
- If I lose this place,
I have nothing to live for.

10:00.774 --> 10:03.341
- Chef, put the knife down,

10:03.385 --> 10:05.039
or my partner's gonna
make sure you never see

10:05.082 --> 10:06.518
the inside
of another kitchen again.

10:06.562 --> 10:08.956
Do you understand me?
Is that the ending you want?

10:08.999 --> 10:10.174
Is it?

10:12.176 --> 10:13.264
Put it down.

10:13.308 --> 10:18.705
♪

10:18.748 --> 10:20.968
[knife clatters]

10:24.493 --> 10:26.713
- First smart decision
you've made all day.

10:30.934 --> 10:31.369
.

10:31.413 --> 10:33.067
- You keep asking.

10:33.110 --> 10:34.155
The doctors keep asking
what drugs I took

10:34.198 --> 10:35.373
because my blood pressure
is heightened.

10:35.417 --> 10:37.071
I don't remember.

10:37.114 --> 10:38.681
I guess I'm in trouble now.

10:38.725 --> 10:41.162
- Yeah, murder is a pretty
big deal, even these days.

10:41.205 --> 10:42.990
- What are you talking about?

10:43.033 --> 10:45.253
- Christina Watkins
was found murdered uptown.

10:45.296 --> 10:47.342
- And you think I did it?

10:47.385 --> 10:48.822
That's crazy.

10:48.865 --> 10:51.825
- You confronted her outside
of the book party.

10:51.868 --> 10:54.392
- I liked Christina.

10:54.436 --> 10:56.743
But when I heard that
they were gonna do the party

10:56.786 --> 11:00.529
at the Yellow Ribbon,
my restaurant--

11:00.572 --> 11:02.705
the book really hurt me.

11:02.749 --> 11:05.012
- Oh, so you put
a hurting on her?

11:05.055 --> 11:06.578
- No.

11:06.622 --> 11:09.930
After we argued,
we went our separate ways.

11:09.973 --> 11:11.409
- Except the woman
you were supposed to

11:11.453 --> 11:13.455
hook up with that night
said you never showed,

11:13.498 --> 11:15.413
and you don't even remember
what drugs you took.

11:15.457 --> 11:17.720
- I didn't do it.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.026
I swear.

11:19.069 --> 11:21.245
- Where'd you go when
the book party broke up?

11:21.289 --> 11:24.205
[suspenseful music]

11:24.248 --> 11:27.338
♪

11:27.382 --> 11:30.254
[upbeat dance music playing]

11:30.298 --> 11:32.648
- This is from 12:20
last night?

11:32.692 --> 11:35.520
- Yeah, Victor came in loaded,
throwing money at the dancers

11:35.564 --> 11:37.087
and bitching about
our food quality.

11:37.131 --> 11:38.654
- How long did he stick around?

11:38.698 --> 11:40.134
- He was still here when I
came in at 10:00 this morning.

11:40.177 --> 11:41.265
- [whistles]

11:41.309 --> 11:42.745
- He passed out
in the VIP room,

11:42.789 --> 11:44.486
so we let him stay 'cause
he's such a loyal customer.

11:44.529 --> 11:46.053
- If Victor's not our guy,
we're back to square one.

11:46.096 --> 11:48.316
[phone buzzes]

11:48.359 --> 11:49.534
- Well, maybe not.

11:49.578 --> 11:50.884
M.E.'s done with the autopsy.

11:50.927 --> 11:53.451
Wants to see us ASAP.

11:53.495 --> 11:55.149
- You were right.

11:55.192 --> 11:58.326
Broken hyoid bone confirms
manual strangulation.

11:58.369 --> 12:01.111
And most of the stab wounds
were post-mortem.

12:01.155 --> 12:05.681
No obvious indicia of fluids
or other DNA sources.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.596
- I stopped listening after
you said "you were right."

12:07.639 --> 12:11.295
- But you missed burn marks
on the back side

12:11.339 --> 12:13.254
and bruising on the torso.

12:13.297 --> 12:15.778
- Uh, yeah, because she was
dressed when we found her.

12:15.822 --> 12:16.953
- Exactly.

12:16.997 --> 12:18.781
Indicating they took her
somewhere else,

12:18.825 --> 12:21.436
undressed her and tortured her,
dressed her again,

12:21.479 --> 12:22.872
and brought her to the park.

12:22.916 --> 12:25.266
Otherwise, there'd still be
more grass on her skin.

12:25.309 --> 12:26.789
- So we were right
about that too.

12:26.833 --> 12:29.313
- Nuh-uh.
Here's what you missed.

12:29.357 --> 12:30.793
[suspenseful music]

12:30.837 --> 12:36.538
A small puncture
from a needle stick.

12:36.581 --> 12:38.279
- So what, she was dosed
with a sedative?

12:38.322 --> 12:41.412
- Well, there's enough propofol
in her to knock over a horse.

12:41.456 --> 12:42.892
- To immobilize her
while he treated her

12:42.936 --> 12:43.980
like a voodoo doll.

12:44.024 --> 12:45.721
- I can't speak
to the psychology,

12:45.765 --> 12:48.724
but I've seen this MO before.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.857
- When?
- A few years ago.

12:50.900 --> 12:54.295
I pulled the case file
before you got here.

12:54.338 --> 12:55.470
- Thank you.

12:58.603 --> 13:02.303
- Oh, you son of a bitch.
You still got all your hair.

13:02.346 --> 13:03.652
- Shaw, meet Jerry Ryan.

13:03.695 --> 13:05.959
I hate to say it,
a great detective

13:06.002 --> 13:07.961
and also godfather
to my daughter, Lily.

13:08.004 --> 13:09.266
- Hey, how you doing?
- How you doing?

13:09.310 --> 13:11.442
- How's Wendy and the kids?
- Oh, she's good.

13:11.486 --> 13:12.792
You know, she's still working,

13:12.835 --> 13:14.576
still doing the church
volunteer thing.

13:14.619 --> 13:17.405
So at least one of us is,
uh, gonna go to heaven.

13:17.448 --> 13:18.798
[all chuckle]

13:18.841 --> 13:20.800
Anyway, this is why I had
you guys come over here.

13:20.843 --> 13:22.845
- Is this the similar case
the M.E. was talking about?

13:22.889 --> 13:25.761
- Yeah, five years ago,
this woman, Li Na Chang,

13:25.805 --> 13:27.371
was found stabbed and strangled

13:27.415 --> 13:29.417
at a Chinatown
hot sheets motel.

13:29.460 --> 13:31.375
- Okay, anything else?

13:31.419 --> 13:33.987
- Yeah, she was doped
with Rohypnol,

13:34.030 --> 13:35.815
tied up, beaten.

13:35.858 --> 13:38.730
Multiple stab wounds,
but no rape.

13:38.774 --> 13:40.384
- Is that it
for the similarities?

13:40.428 --> 13:41.908
- No, that's not it.

13:41.951 --> 13:45.172
I got cases here from
New Jersey, California, London,

13:45.215 --> 13:46.695
all with the same MO.

13:46.738 --> 13:48.001
No rape.

13:48.044 --> 13:51.178
Our guy gets his kicks,
you know, otherwise.

13:51.221 --> 13:52.527
- London?

13:52.570 --> 13:53.876
- Yeah, I get alerts
from Interpol.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.835
- Are those all
the connections, Jerry?

13:55.878 --> 13:57.488
- No!

13:57.532 --> 13:59.360
You think I'd drag you guys
out here on a wild goose chase?

13:59.403 --> 14:01.536
These are copies
I made at Squad.

14:01.579 --> 14:03.712
Take them home.
See for yourself.

14:03.755 --> 14:06.193
This dude is the guy
for all four cases.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.542
I'll bet my shield on it.

14:09.109 --> 14:11.154
- Look, Frank,
I'm not sure I agree

14:11.198 --> 14:13.330
with your friend's theory
tying all these cases together.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.202
Like, the two were robberies,

14:15.245 --> 14:17.726
and none of them
involve propofol

14:17.769 --> 14:19.075
or post-mortem stabbing.

14:19.119 --> 14:20.294
- Okay, okay, I get it.

14:20.337 --> 14:21.686
But I wasn't just
blowing smoke in there.

14:21.730 --> 14:23.036
He's a great cop
with good instincts.

14:23.079 --> 14:25.777
- I'm sure he is,
but right now, he's grasping.

14:25.821 --> 14:27.083
These suspects sketches
can be anybody.

14:27.127 --> 14:29.825
- Okay, but you do see
the similarities

14:29.869 --> 14:31.392
in the victims' looks, right?

14:31.435 --> 14:34.221
They all have dark hair,
strong features.

14:34.264 --> 14:35.570
- Of course I see that,

14:35.613 --> 14:37.006
but they're all from
different backgrounds.

14:37.050 --> 14:38.312
They're all from different
kinds of neighborhoods.

14:38.355 --> 14:39.530
Some of these were planned,

14:39.574 --> 14:40.923
some of these were crimes
of opportunity.

14:40.967 --> 14:43.186
It doesn't make sense.
- Maybe he was escalating.

14:43.230 --> 14:44.535
- To what?

14:44.579 --> 14:46.668
- Escalating with the
brutality of the attacks

14:46.711 --> 14:48.975
and the type of victims
he was selecting.

14:49.018 --> 14:53.457
Going up the social ladder
rung by rung,

14:53.501 --> 14:56.069
getting bolder and bolder
with each murder.

14:56.112 --> 14:57.766
- It's a nice theory.

14:57.809 --> 14:59.550
But based on the evidence
that's available to us,

14:59.594 --> 15:00.943
it's not enough.

15:00.987 --> 15:04.686
- Witnesses describe
a tall white dude in shades

15:04.729 --> 15:06.427
near all the crime scenes.

15:06.470 --> 15:09.343
In Chinatown and California,

15:09.386 --> 15:11.519
witnesses describe also seeing

15:11.562 --> 15:14.696
a tall white dude
driving a black Tesla.

15:14.739 --> 15:17.177
[suspenseful music]

15:17.220 --> 15:18.613
- Hold on.

15:18.656 --> 15:21.094
New Jersey, New Jersey,
Jersey, Jersey.

15:24.010 --> 15:26.577
The witness in the
New Jersey murder

15:26.621 --> 15:29.972
saw a black Tesla
near the crime scene.

15:30.016 --> 15:31.800
The license plate
stuck out to him

15:31.843 --> 15:35.282
because it started
with H-A, like ha,

15:35.325 --> 15:37.153
as if the suspect was laughing.

15:37.197 --> 15:41.549
- Using the same vehicle
in all his killings?

15:41.592 --> 15:43.246
I don't know.

15:43.290 --> 15:45.118
A little too obvious?

15:45.161 --> 15:47.424
- Or a little too brazen.

15:47.468 --> 15:49.818
- This is from the area
around the party that night.

15:49.861 --> 15:51.472
- Aggregated from
Traffic Division.

15:51.515 --> 15:55.084
It's a lot to get through.

15:55.128 --> 15:56.825
- Hold up.
That's a black Tesla.

15:56.868 --> 15:58.653
- How far away is that
from the restaurant?

15:58.696 --> 16:01.047
- A block away,
right before Christina left.

16:03.223 --> 16:05.312
- Show me the area
that's close to where

16:05.355 --> 16:06.791
Christina's phone was tossed.

16:06.835 --> 16:08.402
Maybe there's a better angle
of the plate?

16:08.445 --> 16:11.057
- I was looking before,
but it's a busy street,

16:11.100 --> 16:14.974
and the closest camera
was a quarter mile away.

16:15.017 --> 16:17.193
- Stop. Stop. Right there.

16:17.237 --> 16:19.239
- Let's see who
that's registered to.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.374
- Niles Harper, the actor.

16:24.418 --> 16:26.333
- He wasn't lying.

16:26.376 --> 16:27.725
- About what?

16:27.769 --> 16:29.727
- Not being a hero.

16:36.038 --> 16:36.386
.

16:36.430 --> 16:38.867
- I was supposed to be
on my day off today,

16:38.910 --> 16:40.129
but when you told me about
this Niles Harper guy,

16:40.173 --> 16:41.304
I just--you know,
just kind of went to town.

16:41.348 --> 16:43.263
- What'd I tell you, Shaw?
Dog with a bone.

16:43.306 --> 16:46.092
- I tracked Niles's schedule
of acting jobs

16:46.135 --> 16:49.399
over the past few years
and tried to correlate that

16:49.443 --> 16:51.010
with the pattern
of the serial killer.

16:51.053 --> 16:52.620
- Alleged serial killer.

16:52.663 --> 16:55.492
- Well, just check me on this,
Detective Shaw, okay?

16:55.536 --> 16:56.972
- Mm.
- All right.

16:57.016 --> 17:01.716
So five years ago,
time of the Chinatown murder,

17:01.759 --> 17:04.980
Niles is living in the city
doing theater.

17:05.024 --> 17:09.463
A year later, he's out
in Jersey making a TV show.

17:09.506 --> 17:12.640
And nine miles away,
a cleaning lady gets strangled.

17:12.683 --> 17:15.817
Then, three years ago,
he's outside of LA

17:15.860 --> 17:17.253
making a TV commercial.

17:17.297 --> 17:20.822
A soccer mom
in Joshua Tree gets killed.

17:20.865 --> 17:25.261
And then, two years ago
in London, an ad executive

17:25.305 --> 17:29.091
is killed one mile away
from the set of this

17:29.135 --> 17:33.791
Jack the Ripper movie he's
doing, all with the same MO.

17:33.835 --> 17:35.837
- Getting warmer,
but it's still circumstantial.

17:35.880 --> 17:36.881
- All right, well...

17:36.925 --> 17:38.796
[suspenseful music]

17:38.840 --> 17:39.971
Check that out.

17:40.015 --> 17:43.323
That's from the
Chinatown Motel lobby.

17:43.366 --> 17:45.412
- Uh, I mean,
it could be Niles.

17:45.455 --> 17:46.978
Maybe not. Can't really tell.

17:47.022 --> 17:49.242
- Well, compare it to this.

17:49.285 --> 17:52.158
Look at his wrist.

17:52.201 --> 17:54.073
That's our guy.

17:54.116 --> 17:56.945
You know it, and I know it.

17:56.988 --> 17:59.426
- Okay, let's figure out
where he is right now

17:59.469 --> 18:02.037
so we can talk to him,
get to him

18:02.081 --> 18:05.388
before he lawyers up.

18:05.432 --> 18:07.347
- So sorry we got to talk
on the run, guys,

18:07.390 --> 18:09.827
but, uh, we are way
behind schedule.

18:09.871 --> 18:11.612
Time is money.
- No problem.

18:11.655 --> 18:12.874
Just want to double check on
something about

18:12.917 --> 18:15.137
the last time
you saw Christina.

18:15.181 --> 18:17.096
- Yeah, like I said, I, uh--

18:17.139 --> 18:19.359
I dropped her off at the subway
station on my way uptown.

18:19.402 --> 18:23.058
- That's odd, I don't remember
you saying you gave her a ride.

18:23.102 --> 18:25.843
- I didn't.
- Why's that?

18:25.887 --> 18:28.324
- The woman that was
in my trailer before,

18:28.368 --> 18:30.065
she's my girlfriend.

18:30.109 --> 18:32.372
I just--I didn't feel like
advertising the fact

18:32.415 --> 18:35.157
that I gave Christina
a ride to the subway.

18:35.201 --> 18:36.898
- Are you saying
you and Christina

18:36.941 --> 18:39.205
fooled around in your car?
- No, no, no, no.

18:39.248 --> 18:40.728
I just gave her a ride.

18:40.771 --> 18:44.079
But Megan, my girlfriend,
you know, she's a girl.

18:44.123 --> 18:45.515
She gets jealous.

18:45.559 --> 18:47.169
- Hey, uh, do you mind
if I ask you a question?

18:47.213 --> 18:48.518
- Yeah.

18:48.562 --> 18:50.259
- What is the story with
that thing on your wrist?

18:50.303 --> 18:51.434
- This?
- Yeah.

18:51.478 --> 18:53.480
- I used to have a tat there.

18:53.523 --> 18:55.134
Yeah, a--
[chuckles]

18:55.177 --> 18:58.528
A director asked me to get it
removed for a period picture.

18:58.572 --> 19:00.748
- And they couldn't
just put makeup on it?

19:00.791 --> 19:02.924
- Well, I had a girlfriend
at the time,

19:02.967 --> 19:05.187
and she didn't
like it much, either.

19:05.231 --> 19:08.843
- Hey, uh, what time
did you get home that night?

19:08.886 --> 19:10.236
- Uh, 12:00, 12:30.

19:10.279 --> 19:11.889
Something like that.

19:11.933 --> 19:13.152
Listen, guys,
I got to go to set.

19:13.195 --> 19:15.328
The line producer--
he's gonna murder me.

19:15.371 --> 19:17.286
We can talk more
later if you want.

19:18.548 --> 19:22.509
♪

19:22.552 --> 19:24.511
- What's going on, Jerry?
- You heard him, Frank.

19:24.554 --> 19:27.644
He lied about giving a ride
to Christina that night.

19:27.688 --> 19:30.386
That makes him a legitimate
suspect, which makes this car

19:30.430 --> 19:31.996
a potential crime scene.
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.563
Hey, Jerry, we need a warrant.
You know that.

19:33.607 --> 19:34.695
- We don't have any time.

19:34.738 --> 19:36.305
- What's your
probable cause then?

19:36.349 --> 19:39.352
- Hey, Frank told me you got
a law degree, but we're cops.

19:39.395 --> 19:41.441
So maybe you should
start thinking like

19:41.484 --> 19:43.617
one of us instead of
one of them.

19:43.660 --> 19:45.140
- What the hell's going on?

19:45.184 --> 19:47.447
- We'd like to search your
car if that's okay with you.

19:47.490 --> 19:48.709
- Sorry, I'm running late.

19:48.752 --> 19:51.451
- It'll take two,
three minutes, tops.

19:51.494 --> 19:53.801
- You got a warrant?

19:53.844 --> 19:54.976
- Not yet.

19:57.413 --> 20:00.634
- I see blood.
- Hands off the wheel.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.113
Step out of the vehicle.
- Okay, relax.

20:02.157 --> 20:04.203
- Step out of the vehicle.
- Relax, bro.

20:04.246 --> 20:05.639
I'm just an actor.

20:05.682 --> 20:07.641
There's no blood in there.

20:07.684 --> 20:09.164
- What do you got, Jerry?
Talk to me.

20:09.208 --> 20:12.950
- I saw something red.
Just give me a second.

20:12.994 --> 20:15.779
Frank, right there.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.781
Right on the edge of the mat.

20:17.825 --> 20:19.392
You see it?

20:19.435 --> 20:25.833
♪

20:25.876 --> 20:28.444
- Matches the earring
we found on Christina.

20:33.232 --> 20:35.364
Cuff him.

20:35.408 --> 20:37.105
- What are we doing here,
gentlemen?

20:37.148 --> 20:39.629
My client already told you
he gave Christina Watkins

20:39.673 --> 20:40.674
a ride to the subway.

20:40.717 --> 20:42.806
Big deal. Her earring fell off.

20:42.850 --> 20:44.286
- There was blood
on the earring,

20:44.330 --> 20:46.810
so it didn't exactly fall off.

20:48.508 --> 20:50.031
- He's right. He's right.

20:50.074 --> 20:51.859
I--I didn't want
to admit this before,

20:51.902 --> 20:55.297
but we started kissing
in the car, all right?

20:55.341 --> 20:56.342
And it got physical.

20:56.385 --> 20:58.953
And, uh, she liked it rough.

20:58.996 --> 21:01.042
- That's what you're
gonna tell the judge?

21:01.085 --> 21:03.087
That she liked her earrings
ripped out of her ears?

21:07.396 --> 21:08.571
- We just searched
your apartment,

21:08.615 --> 21:10.704
and we found some
very interesting items.

21:10.747 --> 21:12.706
- [chuckles]
I'm sure you did.

21:12.749 --> 21:14.751
Fans send me
crazy souvenirs all the time.

21:14.795 --> 21:18.233
- Yeah, like a clump
of streaked hair

21:18.277 --> 21:19.756
that was hacked off the victim?

21:19.800 --> 21:24.195
We also found a set
of specialized chef knives

21:24.239 --> 21:25.371
from a limited edition.

21:25.414 --> 21:27.895
Only one of those knives
was missing.

21:27.938 --> 21:31.638
It was a boning knife
with an angular blade--

21:31.681 --> 21:34.945
the kind that was used
to stab Ms. Watkins.

21:34.989 --> 21:40.908
♪

21:40.951 --> 21:41.909
Stand up.

21:47.480 --> 21:50.134
Niles Harper,
you're being charged

21:50.178 --> 21:52.615
with the murder
of Christina Watkins.

21:59.666 --> 21:59.883
.

21:59.927 --> 22:01.668
- Mr. Harper, how do you plead?

22:01.711 --> 22:03.626
- Not guilty, Your Honor.

22:03.670 --> 22:05.106
- Bail?

22:05.149 --> 22:07.195
- Judge, the people
request remand.

22:07.238 --> 22:09.632
The defendant is an
international film star

22:09.676 --> 22:11.373
with an overseas
support network

22:11.417 --> 22:12.896
and projects in countries

22:12.940 --> 22:15.290
without extradition treaties
with the U.S.

22:15.334 --> 22:17.901
- Your Honor, Mr. Harper has
family in the area,

22:17.945 --> 22:19.381
strong ties to the community,

22:19.425 --> 22:20.861
and has made major investments

22:20.904 --> 22:22.732
in struggling parts
of the South Bronx.

22:22.776 --> 22:25.431
- The police found the victim's
bloody earring in his car.

22:25.474 --> 22:27.215
- Mr. Harper
has an airtight alibi

22:27.258 --> 22:28.608
for the night of the murder.

22:28.651 --> 22:31.088
He was at home
with his girlfriend in Tribeca

22:31.132 --> 22:32.742
while Ms. Watkins
was getting killed

22:32.786 --> 22:34.527
on the opposite end
of Manhattan Island.

22:34.570 --> 22:37.399
- Mr. Harper,
given the risk of flight

22:37.443 --> 22:41.055
in the face of these charges,
you are remanded.

22:41.098 --> 22:42.622
[gavel slams]
Next case.

22:46.713 --> 22:48.758
- I just need to ask you
a few things.

22:48.802 --> 22:52.414
- I already said I don't want
to talk to you people.

22:52.458 --> 22:55.896
- Well, then you can testify
in court under subpoena.

22:55.939 --> 22:59.334
- Niles was home by 12:30,
and he was in bed with me

22:59.378 --> 23:01.684
the rest of the night.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.817
- We both know
that isn't the truth.

23:09.126 --> 23:11.564
Look at these.

23:11.607 --> 23:14.305
Look what he did
to these women.

23:14.349 --> 23:15.698
They weren't human to him.

23:15.742 --> 23:19.310
They were just things
he tore up and threw away.

23:19.354 --> 23:20.964
You think this
won't happen to you?

23:21.008 --> 23:22.401
[suspenseful music]

23:22.444 --> 23:24.141
- You're wrong.

23:24.185 --> 23:25.447
There's no way he did this.

23:25.491 --> 23:29.103
- He's a killer, a savage.

23:29.146 --> 23:32.454
He was with me from 12:30 on.

23:32.498 --> 23:36.197
So if you ask me to testify,
that's what I'll say.

23:40.462 --> 23:43.030
- Niles Harper
is a prime example

23:43.073 --> 23:44.771
of the power of celebrity.

23:44.814 --> 23:48.078
People do or say anything
to protect him.

23:48.122 --> 23:50.603
- Can we shake his alibi?

23:50.646 --> 23:52.648
Is there any video
near his house that shows

23:52.692 --> 23:54.737
what time he got home?
- We didn't find anything.

23:54.781 --> 23:57.653
And he turned off his phone
and disabled the GPS in his car

23:57.697 --> 23:59.829
so we can't track
his movements.

23:59.873 --> 24:02.745
- Maybe you can use that
to show consciousness of guilt.

24:04.573 --> 24:07.054
- Bad news--Judge Maldonado
just denied

24:07.097 --> 24:08.359
our Molineux application.

24:08.403 --> 24:09.926
- He rejected it outright?

24:09.970 --> 24:12.842
- We can't mention any
of Niles's prior bad acts.

24:12.886 --> 24:15.541
So nothing about
the other homicides

24:15.584 --> 24:20.023
in New Jersey, London,
California, and Chinatown.

24:20.067 --> 24:25.507
- Okay, so we need to make this
case about Christina Watkins--

24:25.551 --> 24:27.683
and only Christina Watkins.

24:27.727 --> 24:28.902
- Won't be easy.

24:28.945 --> 24:32.427
Niles is a handsome,
charming movie star.

24:32.471 --> 24:34.211
The jurors are gonna have
a hard time believing

24:34.255 --> 24:35.604
he did something this depraved.

24:35.648 --> 24:37.388
- The facts are the facts.

24:37.432 --> 24:39.521
Niles lied about giving
Christina a ride

24:39.565 --> 24:40.827
to the subway that night.

24:40.870 --> 24:43.525
We found clumps of her hair
in his apartment

24:43.569 --> 24:46.876
and her bloody earring
in his car.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.487
We're good, Jack.
The case is strong.

24:48.530 --> 24:49.749
[phone dings]

24:51.925 --> 24:54.449
- Niles's lawyer just filed
a motion to suppress.

25:01.195 --> 25:03.937
- I don't think I've ever
seen a more blatant violation

25:03.980 --> 25:05.547
of the Fourth Amendment
than this search

25:05.591 --> 25:06.592
of my client's car.

25:06.635 --> 25:08.855
No warrant, no probable cause.

25:08.898 --> 25:11.292
- Detective Ryan thought he saw
blood in the defendant's car.

25:11.335 --> 25:12.728
That gave him
probable cause to search.

25:12.772 --> 25:14.730
- And yet,
no blood was ever found.

25:14.774 --> 25:16.297
- They found a bloody earring.

25:16.340 --> 25:17.733
- They should have
got a warrant.

25:17.777 --> 25:20.257
- Mr. Harper was about
to drive away.

25:20.301 --> 25:22.477
That created
exigent circumstances.

25:22.521 --> 25:24.131
- The detective should have
impounded the car

25:24.174 --> 25:25.262
and got a warrant.

25:25.306 --> 25:27.221
- All right, I've heard enough.

25:27.264 --> 25:28.875
I agree with the defense.

25:28.918 --> 25:31.051
- Your Honor,
this is a technicality.

25:31.094 --> 25:33.009
It's inevitable they would
have found the earring.

25:33.053 --> 25:35.969
- The application
to suppress is granted.

25:36.012 --> 25:37.361
- Thank you.

25:37.405 --> 25:39.581
It follows that whatever
they recovered

25:39.625 --> 25:43.106
from my client's apartment--
the hair and the knives--

25:43.150 --> 25:47.241
are fruit of the poison tree
and must be excluded as well.

25:47.284 --> 25:48.285
- Agreed.

25:48.329 --> 25:51.288
[tense music]

25:51.332 --> 25:53.029
♪

25:53.073 --> 25:56.424
- What the hell kind of
prosecutors are you guys?

25:56.467 --> 25:58.078
I thought you knew
what you were doing.

25:58.121 --> 26:00.297
- We're lucky the judge didn't
dismiss the entire case.

26:00.341 --> 26:01.777
- And what is that
supposed to mean?

26:01.821 --> 26:04.084
- You had no right
to enter the car.

26:04.127 --> 26:06.608
- They have a point, Jerry.

26:06.652 --> 26:08.523
- There was no blood
in the car.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.698
- You were not th--
- Okay, okay, okay.

26:09.742 --> 26:12.048
It is what it is.
Let's move on.

26:12.092 --> 26:14.877
Figure out how
we can win this thing.

26:14.921 --> 26:17.358
- Well, I can tap dance
for a few days,

26:17.401 --> 26:18.881
call a medical examiner,

26:18.925 --> 26:21.101
victim's family members
to testify.

26:21.144 --> 26:25.105
But if we don't find some
hard evidence, we're done.

26:25.148 --> 26:26.541
The case will be dismissed.

26:26.585 --> 26:30.066
♪

26:36.159 --> 26:36.333
.

26:36.377 --> 26:37.987
- Talk about a Hail Mary.

26:38.031 --> 26:39.423
- Yeah, you heard
the man, Jerry.

26:39.467 --> 26:42.339
We got two days to the trial,
and we got stugatz.

26:42.383 --> 26:44.603
- This park used to be
a dumping ground

26:44.646 --> 26:46.300
for stolen cars.

26:46.343 --> 26:47.606
You remember that, Frank?

26:47.649 --> 26:49.085
- How did Niles know
about this place anyway?

26:49.129 --> 26:50.086
What did he do?
Shoot a movie here?

26:50.130 --> 26:53.089
- No. No, I already checked.

26:53.133 --> 26:55.265
Hey, buddy!

26:57.920 --> 26:59.095
You got a minute?

26:59.139 --> 27:01.097
- What can I do for you?

27:01.141 --> 27:02.751
I'm Ray.

27:02.795 --> 27:07.451
- You happen to find any knives
around here with that thing?

27:07.495 --> 27:09.323
- No knives.

27:09.366 --> 27:10.629
No guns.

27:10.672 --> 27:13.980
Found a Cadillac fender,
though, two days ago.

27:14.023 --> 27:16.286
Took him straight
across the bridge

27:16.330 --> 27:18.462
to the scrap yards
in the Bronx.

27:18.506 --> 27:21.465
There's not as many scrap yards
as there used to be.

27:21.509 --> 27:24.947
People fixing up those
old warehouses trying to,

27:24.991 --> 27:27.558
uh, you
know, revitalize the area.

27:27.602 --> 27:28.777
- Yeah, thank you
for your time.

27:28.821 --> 27:30.126
I appreciate that.

27:30.170 --> 27:31.475
- That's the way it is
in New York, right?

27:31.519 --> 27:33.652
- That's right.
- Yeah, yeah. Sure, sure.

27:33.695 --> 27:34.957
Things always change.

27:35.001 --> 27:36.480
They always change.

27:36.524 --> 27:39.135
- Didn't Niles's lawyer
say that he was investing

27:39.179 --> 27:40.789
in struggling neighborhoods
in the Bronx?

27:40.833 --> 27:42.486
- Yeah, and she sounded
real proud of it, too,

27:42.530 --> 27:45.576
like it proved her client
was a good guy or something.

27:45.620 --> 27:47.187
- I'm gonna get my phone,
I'm gonna call Yee,

27:47.230 --> 27:49.972
I'm gonna see if she can find
out what properties he owns.

27:50.016 --> 27:52.932
[suspenseful music]

27:52.975 --> 27:59.286
♪

27:59.329 --> 28:01.027
- This is the address.

28:01.070 --> 28:04.030
- License plate reader puts
Niles's car across the street

28:04.073 --> 28:06.119
the night of the murder,
so he was here.

28:11.080 --> 28:13.735
Spread out. Watch yourselves.

28:13.779 --> 28:20.699
♪

28:35.583 --> 28:36.715
- Hey, I got something
over here.

28:38.804 --> 28:39.892
- What do you got?

28:39.935 --> 28:42.198
- One-bedroom apartment.

28:46.986 --> 28:49.423
- Hit that with luminol.

28:49.466 --> 28:51.381
- Niles must have used a tarp
and bleached the hell

28:51.425 --> 28:53.644
out of this place.
I can still smell it.

29:03.611 --> 29:05.395
- No blood.

29:05.439 --> 29:06.875
- All right,
let's keep looking.

29:06.919 --> 29:08.050
Clock is ticking. Let's go.

29:08.094 --> 29:14.100
♪

29:14.143 --> 29:16.102
- Frank, come here.
- Yeah.

29:16.145 --> 29:17.407
I already looked over there.

29:17.451 --> 29:18.582
- No, I think
you missed something.

29:18.626 --> 29:20.671
You, too, Jalen.
Take a look for yourself.

29:33.728 --> 29:34.773
- To Christina.

29:36.470 --> 29:38.907
With love, from Mom.

29:38.951 --> 29:40.213
- We got him, Jerry.

29:40.256 --> 29:41.780
- Yeah, we did. We did.
- We've got him.

29:41.823 --> 29:43.216
- Yeah.

29:47.481 --> 29:49.396
- Most of you
probably recognize

29:49.439 --> 29:51.833
the defendant, Niles Harper.

29:51.877 --> 29:53.617
He's a movie star.

29:53.661 --> 29:57.317
He's played many memorable
and compelling characters.

29:57.360 --> 30:00.668
You've seen him
on the big screen.

30:00.711 --> 30:01.712
You like him.

30:03.279 --> 30:06.500
But you don't really know him.

30:06.543 --> 30:12.723
The actual Niles Harper is a
violent and sadistic predator

30:12.767 --> 30:16.858
who saw Christina Watkins at a
party, lured her into his car,

30:16.902 --> 30:20.253
then tortured and killed her
in a warehouse

30:20.296 --> 30:21.732
he owns in the Bronx.

30:24.605 --> 30:26.868
The evidence against the
defendant is substantial.

30:26.912 --> 30:29.262
He lied to the police
on numerous occasions

30:29.305 --> 30:31.133
when trying to explain
his whereabouts

30:31.177 --> 30:32.700
on the night of the murder.

30:32.743 --> 30:36.835
Even more damning, the police
found Christina's necklace

30:36.878 --> 30:39.533
in the defendant's warehouse,
which just so happens

30:39.576 --> 30:42.188
to be located a quarter mile
from the park

30:42.231 --> 30:45.365
where her mutilated corpse
was found.

30:45.408 --> 30:47.933
Ladies and gentlemen,

30:47.976 --> 30:50.413
don't make the same mistake

30:50.457 --> 30:53.547
Christina Watkins made.

30:53.590 --> 30:55.375
Don't let Niles Harper
fool you into thinking

30:55.418 --> 31:00.641
he's a good person
because he's not.

31:00.684 --> 31:05.211
He's a violent,
vicious murderer.

31:12.000 --> 31:16.004
- I agree with much of what
Mr. Price just said.

31:16.048 --> 31:19.399
This case is full of illusions.

31:19.442 --> 31:22.576
But it's the evidence
against my client

31:22.619 --> 31:24.926
that is the illusion.

31:24.970 --> 31:26.797
They have nothing.

31:26.841 --> 31:32.064
No witnesses, no forensics,
no confession.

31:32.107 --> 31:33.935
And to make matters worse,

31:33.979 --> 31:37.808
this case is rife
with police misconduct.

31:37.852 --> 31:40.202
We used to always
give the police

31:40.246 --> 31:42.378
the benefit of the doubt.

31:42.422 --> 31:44.076
Not anymore.

31:44.119 --> 31:49.211
Scrutinize every word that
comes out of their mouths,

31:49.255 --> 31:52.432
because we've seen what they do

31:52.475 --> 31:56.001
when they think
no one is looking.

31:56.044 --> 31:58.960
Don't let them get away
with it this time.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.963
[tense music]

32:02.007 --> 32:05.967
♪

32:06.011 --> 32:08.056
- Have Cosgrove reach out
to Christina's mother.

32:08.100 --> 32:10.754
We need to nail down
some of these details.

32:14.106 --> 32:16.412
- I'm sorry, I don't keep track
of things too well.

32:16.456 --> 32:18.414
I don't get a whole lot
of sleep these days.

32:18.458 --> 32:20.155
Uh, remind me what it
is I'm looking for.

32:20.199 --> 32:22.288
- I'm looking for credit card
statements or receipts

32:22.331 --> 32:23.680
that would show
that you purchased

32:23.724 --> 32:25.073
that necklace for Christina.

32:25.117 --> 32:26.466
- Right, sorry.

32:26.509 --> 32:28.772
I just remembered
I paid cash for it.

32:28.816 --> 32:31.297
Does that hurt the case?
- It's not a big problem.

32:31.340 --> 32:33.908
We still have the necklace.
It's a good piece of evidence.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.605
- Thank God.

32:35.649 --> 32:37.607
I just want to make sure that
that monster pays

32:37.651 --> 32:39.783
for what he did to my Tina,

32:39.827 --> 32:42.612
and that he never does it
to anyone else's daughter.

32:44.310 --> 32:47.269
- Patti, we all feel
the same way.

32:47.313 --> 32:48.488
- I know you do.

32:51.491 --> 32:53.797
Jerry spoke so highly of you.

32:53.841 --> 32:55.669
- Jerry?

32:55.712 --> 32:57.845
I didn't know you spoke
with Detective Ryan.

32:57.888 --> 32:58.977
- Yeah, he came by
the other day

32:59.020 --> 33:00.935
just to check and see
how I was doing.

33:04.504 --> 33:06.549
Wait, did I say
something wrong?

33:06.593 --> 33:08.160
- Oh, no, not at all.

33:08.203 --> 33:09.422
Not at all.

33:09.465 --> 33:10.989
Let's see if we can
find that receipt.

33:15.515 --> 33:16.995
Next round's on you.

33:17.038 --> 33:18.387
Bottoms up, my friend.

33:21.042 --> 33:23.131
By the way, I didn't realize
you stopped by

33:23.175 --> 33:25.003
and saw Christina's mother.

33:25.046 --> 33:27.483
- Oh, that's what
I always told you.

33:27.527 --> 33:29.007
You stay in touch
with the victim's family

33:29.050 --> 33:30.573
because you never know
when somebody's gonna

33:30.617 --> 33:32.662
remember something useful.
- Good advice.

33:32.706 --> 33:34.316
That's why I was
surprised you didn't ask

33:34.360 --> 33:35.709
me and Shaw to come with.

33:35.752 --> 33:37.493
We were supposed to be
primaries on the case.

33:39.234 --> 33:41.019
- Is this about your ego,
Frank?

33:41.062 --> 33:42.672
- No, it's about
the fact that you went by

33:42.716 --> 33:44.500
and saw Christina's mother now

33:44.544 --> 33:46.067
before we searched
the warehouse.

33:46.111 --> 33:49.549
♪

33:49.592 --> 33:50.854
- What are you saying?

33:50.898 --> 33:53.031
- That spot where
we found the necklace,

33:53.074 --> 33:56.382
I searched that area a minute
before and it wasn't there.

33:58.340 --> 34:00.864
- [scoffs]
You're confused.

34:03.780 --> 34:05.521
Ahh.

34:05.565 --> 34:07.741
I need a refill.

34:07.784 --> 34:10.048
- Jerry.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.005
Jerry, it's me.

34:13.486 --> 34:16.706
This is not the way we do it.

34:16.750 --> 34:20.101
- I have been doing it
the right way for 32 years.

34:20.145 --> 34:22.060
The necklace was there.

34:22.103 --> 34:23.974
You just missed it.

34:24.018 --> 34:30.938
♪

34:44.256 --> 34:44.473
.

34:44.517 --> 34:46.997
- Can you tell us what we're
looking at here, Detective?

34:47.041 --> 34:48.695
- It's footage
from a three-hour window

34:48.738 --> 34:51.219
around the time
that Niles Harper told us

34:51.263 --> 34:53.134
that he dropped
Christina Watkins

34:53.178 --> 34:54.570
off of the subway station.

34:54.614 --> 34:57.791
- And does Christina Watkins
appear in it at any time?

34:57.834 --> 34:59.314
- No, she does not.

35:01.273 --> 35:02.578
- What are we looking at here?

35:02.622 --> 35:05.277
- That's an image
from NYPD Auto Crime

35:05.320 --> 35:07.714
around 2:00 a.m.
that same night

35:07.757 --> 35:10.195
when they were in the area
looking for stolen cars.

35:10.238 --> 35:12.066
- Can you identify the car?

35:12.110 --> 35:15.200
- It's a vehicle registered to
Niles Harper parked in front

35:15.243 --> 35:17.245
of the warehouse
he owns in the Bronx

35:17.289 --> 35:20.770
at a time when he claimed
he was home in bed.

35:20.814 --> 35:26.167
- The same Bronx warehouse
where this necklace was found?

35:26.211 --> 35:28.865
- Yes.
We were searching the premises.

35:28.909 --> 35:32.478
I noticed something glimmer
under a tool cabinet.

35:32.521 --> 35:34.871
I called over
Detectives Cosgrove and Shaw.

35:34.915 --> 35:39.659
Detective Shaw reached down
and found the necklace

35:39.702 --> 35:41.965
and read the inscription.

35:42.009 --> 35:43.706
"To Christina.

35:43.750 --> 35:46.318
With love, from Mom."

35:46.361 --> 35:48.537
- Thank you.
No further questions.

35:50.235 --> 35:52.324
- Counselor.

35:52.367 --> 35:56.197
- Detective Ryan,
are you modest?

35:57.981 --> 36:02.464
- Uh, no, not particularly.

36:02.508 --> 36:05.119
I'm a detective first grade.

36:05.163 --> 36:07.687
Means I'm really good
at my job.

36:07.730 --> 36:09.210
- Mm.

36:09.254 --> 36:12.909
And yet you credit
Detective Shaw

36:12.953 --> 36:15.869
with finding the necklace.

36:15.912 --> 36:19.568
But you were the one who
spotted it first, didn't you?

36:19.612 --> 36:21.091
- I did.

36:21.135 --> 36:22.528
- Even though
the other officers

36:22.571 --> 36:24.617
had already looked in the area?

36:24.660 --> 36:27.359
- Well, that can happen
in a rush.

36:28.751 --> 36:31.841
- Detective,
you planted that necklace

36:31.885 --> 36:33.321
in the warehouse, didn't you?

36:34.670 --> 36:36.629
- No.

36:36.672 --> 36:38.674
- You remember you're
under oath, don't you?

36:38.718 --> 36:41.721
The penalties for tampering
and perjury are serious.

36:41.764 --> 36:43.113
- I know the law.

36:43.157 --> 36:45.246
- You hate my client,
don't you?

36:45.290 --> 36:48.554
- I hate people
who murder women.

36:48.597 --> 36:52.122
So, yeah, I don't
care for him too much.

36:52.166 --> 36:54.212
- And you'd do anything

36:54.255 --> 36:56.518
to ensure he's convicted,
wouldn't you?

36:56.562 --> 36:58.085
- No.

36:58.128 --> 37:00.218
I'm an honest cop.

37:00.261 --> 37:02.307
I do it the right way.

37:02.350 --> 37:03.786
But you already know that.

37:05.571 --> 37:11.664
- This is a photo taken
the night of the murder.

37:11.707 --> 37:14.406
[tense music]

37:14.449 --> 37:16.973
As you can see,
Christina isn't wearing

37:17.017 --> 37:20.281
the necklace you claim
to have found in the warehouse.

37:23.066 --> 37:26.113
So if she's not wearing it,

37:26.156 --> 37:27.854
how did it end up
in a warehouse

37:27.897 --> 37:29.116
a few hours later?

37:29.159 --> 37:32.293
- Could have been in her purse,

37:32.337 --> 37:35.209
her pocket, her hand.

37:35.253 --> 37:36.297
Who knows?

37:36.341 --> 37:38.517
But it was there.

37:38.560 --> 37:41.955
We found it in the warehouse.

37:41.998 --> 37:43.304
That's a fact.

37:43.348 --> 37:45.263
- You finding it is a fact.

37:45.306 --> 37:47.308
That doesn't mean
you didn't plant it.

37:47.352 --> 37:49.310
- Objection.
She's badgering the witness.

37:49.354 --> 37:51.312
- Sustained.

37:51.356 --> 37:53.271
Move on, Ms. Hunt.

37:53.314 --> 37:54.620
- Nothing further.

37:54.663 --> 37:56.317
The defense rests, Your Honor.

37:56.361 --> 37:58.798
- Court is adjourned
for the jury to deliberate.

37:58.841 --> 37:59.973
[gavel slams]

38:00.016 --> 38:06.936
♪

38:09.417 --> 38:12.855
- Frank, if you got something
to tell me, tell me now.

38:16.511 --> 38:18.557
- We got our man, Jalen.

38:18.600 --> 38:20.559
That's all you need to know.

38:39.534 --> 38:41.362
- Has the jury
reached a verdict?

38:41.406 --> 38:42.581
- We have, Your Honor.

38:42.624 --> 38:44.800
- Will the defendant
please rise?

38:48.587 --> 38:50.502
- In the charge of murder
in the second degree,

38:50.545 --> 38:53.461
we find the defendant,
Niles Harper, guilty.

38:56.638 --> 38:59.902
- Members of the jury,
thank you for your service.

38:59.946 --> 39:01.861
Court is adjourned.

39:01.904 --> 39:03.036
[gavel slams]

39:03.079 --> 39:05.952
[indistinct chatter]

39:11.261 --> 39:12.698
- Ma'am.
- Thank you.

39:15.091 --> 39:17.398
Thank you.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.313
Thank you so much.

39:19.357 --> 39:26.407
♪

39:40.334 --> 39:42.510
- Something smells good.

39:42.554 --> 39:44.643
I brought dessert.

39:44.686 --> 39:45.731
- Good.

39:45.774 --> 39:47.559
Mom put out an extra setting.

39:47.602 --> 39:50.300
Uncle Jerry
is here to celebrate.

39:57.220 --> 39:58.526
- What do you say, Frank?

39:58.570 --> 40:00.398
All's well that ends well, huh?

40:00.441 --> 40:02.487
- Honey, take this in
to your mom.

40:02.530 --> 40:03.662
Tell her to hold off on dinner.

40:03.705 --> 40:06.839
I need to talk
to your godfather.

40:06.882 --> 40:08.580
- Okay.

40:08.623 --> 40:11.539
Dinner's almost ready.

40:11.583 --> 40:14.499
- Well, really went
for it this time.

40:14.542 --> 40:19.504
18-year-old single malt,
sherry cask, the whole deal.

40:19.547 --> 40:21.114
Cost me 400 bucks,

40:21.157 --> 40:23.290
but the guy said
it was worth it.

40:23.333 --> 40:25.292
Here you go.

40:25.335 --> 40:27.381
♪

40:27.425 --> 40:28.556
What's wrong?

40:28.600 --> 40:30.863
- I can't accept this.

40:30.906 --> 40:32.908
- Frank, why not?

40:32.952 --> 40:35.998
Frank, justice
was served today.

40:38.392 --> 40:40.307
- You need to leave.

40:40.350 --> 40:47.488
♪

40:51.231 --> 40:54.800
Jerry, you need to leave.

41:05.941 --> 41:07.682
[sighs]

41:14.950 --> 41:17.866
[dramatic music]

41:17.910 --> 41:24.873
♪

41:44.980 --> 41:47.896
[wolf howls]
